Simple netlink communication between a kernel module and a process 3.13

Installing the linux headers

You need to install the linux-headers-.. first as shown below. Depending on your distro, use apt-get or yum.

# apt-get install build-essential linux-headers-$(uname -r)

Next, create the following netlink.c module in C programming language.Create the following user.c module in C programming language.

reate Makefile to Compile Kernel Module

The following makefile can be used to compile the above simple netlink communication between a kernel module and a process 3.13

Use the make command to compile  netlink communication as shown below.
